    "body": "### Describe your issue\n\nIt's currently fuzzy what is a \"safe node\" when it comes to duplicating subtrees and which nodes need to be coerced to a temp. There should be a general way to let nodes declare that they are safe in that regard rather than listing certain node types in an ad-hoc fashion and forgetting about others.\n\nHere's an incomplete list:\n- literals\n- non-global (non-temp) names\n- certain temp nodes with fixed results\n- `RawCNameExprNode` ?\n- … ?",
